<th style="background:#6495ED;">29</th>
<td><a href="/wiki/Erin_O%27Toole" title="Erin O'Toole">Erin O'Toole</a></td>
<td>January 5, 2015</td>
<td><i>Incumbent</i></td>
<td>Conservative</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p>Prior to 1944, the responsibilities of the current Veterans Affairs portfolio were part of the now-defunct post of <a href="/wiki/Minister_of_Pensions_and_National_Health" title="Minister of Pensions and National Health" class="mw-redirect">Minister of Pensions and National Health</a>.</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Military_Service">Military Service</span></h2>
<p>A few ministers have had prior military experience, although the posting does not require it:</p>
<table class="wikitable">
<tr>
<th>Name</th>
<th>Branch, Unit</th>
<th>Rank</th>
<th>Service Period</th>
